<!-- Introduction -->
	<purpose>
	<p>
	This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the identification of the shape of an object and portions of that shape and to characterize with properties a shape or shape portion.
	</p>
</purpose>
	
	<inscope>
      <li>identification of an object that may have properties but cannot be considered as a product or an activity;</li>
      <li>concept of shape of an object;</li>
      <li>identification of a portion of a shape;</li>
      <li>relationship between two portions of shape;</li>
      <li>shape of an object in the context of a particular occurrence of that object in a product structure;</li>
      <li>association of a representation with a shape or shape portion;</li>
      <li>assignment of shape related properties to a shape or to a shape portion;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="assembly_structure:1_scope">Assembly structure</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1026;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="external_model:1_scope">External model</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1033;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="geometric_model_relationship:1_scope">Geometric model relationship</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1403;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:1_scope">Product view definition relationship</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1041.</li>
   </inscope>
